            <h2 class="section-title">In-Depth Performance</h2>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h3>Image Quality & Sensor Performance</h3>
                <p>
                    The 20-megapixel stacked BSI CMOS sensor is optimized for speed rather than resolution, but image quality remains impressive. The stacked design enables remarkable readout speeds while maintaining low noise and excellent dynamic range‚Äîapproximately 12.5 stops at base ISO. Colors are accurate with a neutral rendering that responds well to editing.
                </p>
                <p>
                    High-ISO performance is strong for Micro Four Thirds‚ÄîISO 3200 produces clean images with minimal noise, and ISO 6400 remains highly usable. The computational High Res Shot mode combines 8 images to produce 50MP (handheld) or 80MP (tripod) files with exceptional detail. This effectively eliminates the resolution disadvantage of MFT for static subjects like landscapes and architecture.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h3>Autofocus & Tracking System</h3>
                <p>
                    The OM-1 II features a revolutionary 1,053-point cross-type quad-pixel AF system with AI-powered subject detection. The camera recognizes humans (face/eye/torso), animals (dogs, cats, birds), vehicles (cars, motorcycles, airplanes, helicopters, trains), and even insects. Bird detection is particularly impressive‚Äîthe camera locks onto small, fast-moving subjects with remarkable accuracy.
                </p>
                <p>
                    With 120 fps continuous shooting (AF/AE tracking at every frame), the OM-1 II captures moments no other camera can. Pro Capture mode buffers up to 70 frames before the shutter is pressed, eliminating timing mistakes entirely. The C-AF tracking algorithm sticks to subjects tenaciously, even through obstacles and rapid direction changes. Low-light AF works reliably to -6 EV with the 12-40mm f/2.8 attached.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h3>Video Capabilities</h3>
                <p>
                    Video features are comprehensive for a camera focused on still photography. Internal 4K 60p recording with 10-bit 4:2:2 delivers professional quality, while 4K 120p enables dramatic slow motion without external recorders. OM-Log400 provides flat footage with approximately 12 stops of dynamic range for color grading. Rolling shutter is well-controlled thanks to the stacked sensor architecture.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The 5-axis in-body stabilization is exceptional in video mode‚Äîhandheld footage is remarkably smooth, approaching gimbal-like quality in many situations. No recording time limits apply, and heat management is excellent for a compact body. Focus breathing is minimal with PRO series lenses. The main limitation is the 1.5x crop in 4K 60p mode, though oversampled 4K 30p uses the full sensor width.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
