                <p>
                    The OM-1 II inherits OM System's legendary weather sealing‚ÄîIP53 rated, tested to -10¬∞C, and virtually indestructible in the field. The magnesium alloy body with extensive sealing handles rain, snow, dust, and harsh conditions that would disable other cameras. The deep grip accommodates even the large 40-150mm f/2.8 PRO telephoto without strain.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Battery life is excellent for a mirrorless camera‚Äîapproximately 500 shots per charge (CIPA)‚Äîwith real-world performance often exceeding 800 shots. The BLX-1 battery is shared with other OM System cameras. The 2.36M-dot EVF is fast with minimal blackout, essential for 120fps burst shooting. Overall weight of 599g (body + battery) makes this the most portable professional wildlife/sports system available.
                </p>
